gomodel:SYNGO_5517  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: biochemical fractions of whole adult rat brain show p39 (CDK5R2) is present synaptic subfractions S2 (crude synaptosome), P3 (Golgi, ER), LP1 (synaptic membranes).\n\nFigure 3a: \"Thin mouse cerebellar sections were incubated with affinity purified p39 (CDK5R2) polyclonal antibody and viewed by transmission electron microscopy. Arrowheads point to gold particles revealing the presence of p39 near the synaptic junction.\"\n\nFigure 3b: \"3 weeks old hippocampal cultures were stained with anti-p39 and anti-synapsin II antibodies. Partial co-localization of p39 and synapsin is observed.\". Experimental description: Figure 3: \"Thin mouse cerebellar sections were incubated with affinity purified p39 polyclonal antibody and\nviewed by transmission electron microscopy\"\n\n\"The rabbit polyclonal p39 [12] was raised by immunization of rabbits with an N-terminal truncation of human p39 (amino acids 111±367) fused to a 6-histidine tag and was affinity purified on a GST-p39 column. The actin rabbit polyclonal antibody (Sigma), the p35 antibody C19 (Santa Cruz), the cdk5 mouse monoclonal antibody DC17 (Kinetek Biology Corporation) and the monoclonal PSD-95 antibody (Upstate Biotechnology) were used for Western blot.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5517" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

